Here's how to implement all three requirements:

### 1. Custom "Cancel" back button on `EditProductPage`

```xml
<!-- EditProductPage.xaml -->
<ContentPage ...>
    <Shell.BackButtonBehavior>
        <BackButtonBehavior TextOverride="Cancel"
                           Command="{Binding CancelCommand}" />
    </Shell.BackButtonBehavior>
    <!-- your form content -->
</ContentPage>
```

### 2. ViewModel with confirmation logic

```csharp
public partial class EditProductViewModel : ObservableObject
{
    [ObservableProperty]
    bool hasUnsavedChanges;

    [RelayCommand]
    async Task Cancel()
    {
        if (hasUnsavedChanges)
        {
            bool discard = await Shell.Current.DisplayAlert(
                "Unsaved Changes",
                "Discard changes and go back?",
                "Discard", "Stay");
            if (!discard) return;
        }
        await Shell.Current.GoToAsync("..");
    }
}
```

### 3. Guard the system back gesture/button too

The custom `BackButtonBehavior` handles the toolbar button, but the user can also swipe back or press the hardware back button. Guard that in `AppShell.xaml.cs`:

```csharp
protected override async void OnNavigating(ShellNavigatingEventArgs args)
{
    base.OnNavigating(args);

    if (args.Source == ShellNavigationSource.Pop
        && Shell.Current.CurrentPage is EditProductPage page
        && page.BindingContext is EditProductViewModel vm
        && vm.HasUnsavedChanges)
    {
        var deferral = args.GetDeferral();
        bool discard = await DisplayAlert(
            "Unsaved Changes",
            "Discard changes and go back?",
            "Discard", "Stay");
        if (!discard)
            args.Cancel();
        deferral.Complete();
    }
}
```

**Key points:**
- `BackButtonBehavior.Command` replaces the default back action entirely — your command must call `GoToAsync("..")` itself.
- `OnNavigating` with `GetDeferral()` catches swipe-back and hardware back. The deferral is required because `DisplayAlert` is async.
- Check `args.Source == ShellNavigationSource.Pop` so the guard only fires on back navigation, not forward.
